text: Pyrausta quadrimaculalis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Paul Dognin in 1908. It is found in Argentina. ==Taxonomy== The name quadrimaculalis is preoccupied by Pyrausta quadrimaculalis described by South in 1901. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1908 quadrimaculalis (Dognin, 1908) Category:Moths of South America
title: Pyrausta quadrimaculalis (Dognin, 1908)
